nodes.text: Catherine Anne "Cat" Taber (born December 30, 1979) is an American actress appearing in films, television and video games. Since 2003, she has done voice acting, including several Star Wars projects. Her main works included voicing Mission Vao in Star Wars: Knights of the Old Republic, Padmé Amidala in Star Wars: The Clone Wars, Vette in Star Wars: The Old Republic, and Numa in Star Wars Rebels.
